snippet: A worker fell about 25 feet at a construction site in Kew Gardens and was trapped in waist-deep mud over three hours, fire officials said.
abstract: Construction worker falls 25 feet into trench at construction site in Queens, and is trapped waist-deep in mud for over three hours before rescuers pull him out; man’s co-workers tried for an hour to free him before calling rescuers.

byline.original: By MICHAEL SCHWIRTZ and NATE SCHWEBER

lead_paragraph: A worker fell about 25 feet at a construction site in Kew Gardens and was trapped in waist-deep mud over three hours, fire officials said.

headline.main: Queens Worker Pulled From Mud After Fall Into Trench
headline.print_headline: Worker Pulled From Mud After Fall Into Trench
